<TITLE> PM vows to curb terror </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina in her first question-answer session in parliament on Wednesday assured the House that she would curb militancy and bring perpetrators to justice. The PM said she would not hesitate to take action against any bank or other institutions involved in funding militant activities. Hasina said her government had taken steps for the formation of a "South Asian Interior Taskforce" to tackle cross border terror, in line with her party's election manifesto. "Militants have no religion and border. They are against religion and humanity," she said, replying to a question from Md Tajul Islam MP who raised the first question of the ninth parliament. "I have already instructed the relevant ministries to tackle the roots of militancy and ordered law enforcers to be active against them," she said. The prime minister said she had instructed intelligence agencies to uncover their sources of money, arms and their patrons. "I have instructed authorities concerned to take measures for the formation of the South Asian Interior Taskforce," she said. "It will help us to root out the militants and bring them to justice." bdnews2
